model_explanation: if Sam only gave Tom apples, then giving Tom grapes contradicts that “only” condition.
the statement about Mary’s bananas and the statement about Bill’s bananas refer to different people and are independent.
the claim that Sam only gave Mary apples is contradicted by the statement that he also gave her bananas.
giving apples to Sue and not giving them to Rob are separate pieces of information about different individuals and are independent.
the “only” statement excludes the possibility of giving something else to Bill, and giving him grapes contradicts that.
if Sam only gave Rob grapes, it follows logically that he didn’t give Rob apples. That is entailed.
giving Sue grapes and also giving Tom grapes are independent pieces of information about different people.
the statement about Ellen receiving grapes does not provide information about Rob. The two are independent.
